definition:
Someone descended from Iezer, a man of the tribe of Manasseh living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Num.26.30; 
 son of: Gilead (H1568H); 
 brother of: Helek (H2507), Asriel (H0844), Shechem (H7928), Shemida (H8061) and Hepher (H2660A); also called Iezer (KJV: Jeezer) at Num.26.30; 
Group of a.vi.e.zer (אֲבִיעֶ֫זֶר "Abiezer" H0044I) 
 § Jeezerite = "no help"
 one of the tribe of Jeezer
